@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

left to right direction
title FIG-09-03. Horizon Bank Payment Routing DRD

skinparam nodesep 75
skinparam ranksep 75

rectangle "Payment Instruction\n<<Input Data>>" as PaymentInstruction #FFFFFF
rectangle "Account Status\n<<Input Data>>" as AccountStatus #FFFFFF
rectangle "Screening Result\n<<Input Data>>" as ScreeningResult #FFFFFF
rectangle "Payment Cut-Off Status\n<<Input Data>>" as CutoffStatus #FFFFFF

rectangle "Information\nrequirements" as InfoReq #FFFFFF
rectangle "Payment Routing Rules\n<<Business Knowledge Model>>" as RoutingRules #EAF6E8
rectangle "Payments Operations Policy\n<<Knowledge Source>>" as PaymentsPolicy #FFF4D6
rectangle "Financial Crime Screening Policy\n<<Knowledge Source>>" as ScreeningPolicy #FFF4D6

rectangle "Determine Payment Route\n<<Decision>>\n\nResult: Proceed, Repair,\nManual Review or Reject" as PaymentRoute #DDEEFF

PaymentInstruction -down[hidden]-> AccountStatus
AccountStatus -down[hidden]-> ScreeningResult
ScreeningResult -down[hidden]-> CutoffStatus
CutoffStatus -right[hidden]-> InfoReq
InfoReq -right[hidden]-> PaymentRoute
PaymentsPolicy -down[hidden]-> ScreeningPolicy
ScreeningPolicy -down[hidden]-> RoutingRules

PaymentInstruction --> InfoReq
AccountStatus --> InfoReq
ScreeningResult --> InfoReq
CutoffStatus --> InfoReq
InfoReq -right-> PaymentRoute : info req
RoutingRules -right-> PaymentRoute : knowledge req
PaymentsPolicy -right-> RoutingRules : authority req
ScreeningPolicy -right-> RoutingRules : authority req

legend bottom
DMN-style decision requirements teaching view.
info req = information requirement; knowledge req = knowledge requirement; authority req = authority requirement.
Arrows point from required information, knowledge or authority to the decision or governed element.
This is not process sequence and not semantic .dmn XML.
endlegend
@enduml
